The National Security Memorandum (NSM-15) outlines the United States' policy to counter biological threats, enhance pandemic preparedness, and achieve global health security. It emphasizes that the US and the world are vulnerable to biological threats, as highlighted by the COVID-19 pandemic. The memo states that countering biological threats is a top national and international security priority. It calls for the transformation of capabilities to protect the nation from biological threats and promote pandemic preparedness and health security globally. The memo also establishes coordination and governance mechanisms for US biodefense efforts, with the Assistant to the President for National Security Affairs leading policy coordination and review. It directs agencies to implement the Biodefense Strategy and related strategies and to coordinate with other agencies involved in biodefense. The memo also outlines requirements for budgeting, information sharing, and threat assessments. It replaces a previous memorandum and is subject to applicable laws and appropriations.